  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\nIn current [tests/beacon/conftest.py](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/c78020fe0cf6b4d98b93264872dfd10c59757e06/tests/beacon/conftest.py#L135-L196), these fixtures are for setting configuration variables via `parametrize`, but still, strange.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/pull/1338#discussion_r221757203 by Piper\r\n\r\nRemoving the `config` *global* concept towards a `constants` module and configurable class based approach.\r\n\r\nI.E. The `cycle_length` would be part of some class and retrieved with `BeaconChain.get_cycle_length()` with the default implementation returning `constants.CYCLE_LENGTH`.\r\n\r\n- Easy to modify at runtime\r\n- easy to integrate into the chain builder API\r\n- avoids the use of globals\r\n- doesn't require passing around a config object (which will result in annoying dependencies based on my experience\r\n",
